'''1629–1631年意大利鼠疫'''（英文：1629–1631 Italian Plague），也称“'''米兰大鼠疫'''（Great Plague of Milan）”是指于1629年-1631年间在[[意大利|意大利]]北部和中部地区爆发的一系列[[鼠疫|鼠疫]]疫情，属[[第二次鼠疫大流行|第二次鼠疫大流行]]的疫情<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Empirical "integrated disease management" in Ferrara during the Italian plague (1629-1631)|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31887395/|last=Vicentini|first=Chiara Beatrice|last2=Manfredini|first2=Stefano|date=2020-04|journal=Parasitology International|doi=10.1016/j.parint.2019.102046|volume=75|pages=102046|issn=1873-0329|pmid=31887395|last3=Mares|first3=Donatella|last4=Bonacci|first4=Teresa|last5=Scapoli|first5=Chiara|last6=Chicca|first6=Milvia|last7=Pezzi|first7=Marco|access-date=2021-01-21|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108215044/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31887395/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Review of Cristofano and the Plague. A Study in the History of Public Health in the Age of Galileo|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/2860436|last=Rosen|first=George|date=1975|journal=Renaissance Quarterly|issue=1|doi=10.2307/2860436|volume=28|pages=83–86|issn=0034-4338|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206235044/https://www.jstor.org/stable/2860436}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite journal|title=Plague in seventeenth-century Europe and the decline of Italy: an epidemiological hypothesis|author=Guido Alfani|url=https://academic.oup.com/ereh/article/17/4/408/499216|journal=European Review of Economic History|issue=4|doi=|others=|year=2013|volume=17|page=408–430|pmid=|access-date=2021-01-21|archive-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804201459/https://academic.oup.com/ereh/article/17/4/408/499216|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=A tragedy of the great plague of Milan in 1630 - Digital Collections - National Library of Medicine|url=https://collections.nlm.nih.gov/catalog/nlm:nlmuid-101627450-bk|accessdate=2020-12-20|work=collections.nlm.nih.gov}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=人类历史上的大瘟疫|url=http://paper.people.com.cn/rmzk/html/2020-03/04/content_1974584.htm|accessdate=2020-12-20|author=|date=2020年|format=|work=|publisher=《人民周刊》|agency=[[人民网|人民网]]|language=zh|archive-date=2020-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200714025740/http://paper.people.com.cn/rmzk/html/2020-03/04/content_1974584.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此次疫情是[[欧洲|欧洲]][[黑死病|黑死病]]后的一次重大鼠疫疫情，约造成了100万人死亡、约占意大利总人口的25%，是历史上[[流行病列表|致死人数最多的流行病之一]]<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite book|chapter=|url=http://archive.org/details/epidemicspandemi0000hays|publisher=Santa Barbara, Calif. : ABC-CLIO|date=2005|isbn=978-1-85109-658-9|first=J. N.|last=Hays|title=Epidemics and pandemics : their impacts on human history|year=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=History's deadliest pandemics, from ancient Rome to modern America|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2020/local/retropolis/coronavirus-deadliest-pandemics/|accessdate=2020-12-20|author=|date=|format=|work=Washington Post|publisher=|language=en|archive-date=2020-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200407204000/https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2020/local/retropolis/coronavirus-deadliest-pandemics/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。也学者认为此次疫情造成了意大利国力的衰弱<ref name=":1" />。

== 历史 ==
由于欧洲的“[[三十年战争|三十年战争]]”（1618年－1648年），1629年，[[德国|德国]]和[[法国|法国]]的军队调度将鼠疫疫情带到了[[意大利|意大利]]的[[曼托瓦|曼托瓦]]<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=http://archive.org/details/encyclopediaplag00kohn|publisher=New York : Facts On File|date=2008|isbn=978-0-8160-6935-4|last=Kohn|first=George C.|title=Encyclopedia of plague and pestilence : from ancient times to the present|year=|location=|pages=}}</ref>。受感染的威尼斯军队随后撤退到意大利的中部和北部地区，导致疫情扩散。

1629年10月，疫情蔓延至[[伦巴第大区|伦巴第大区]]的商业中心——[[米兰|米兰]]。尽管米兰进行了有效的[[公共卫生|公共卫生]]防疫措施，譬如[[隔离检疫|隔离]]、限制商品交易等，但疫情依然在隐蔽传播。直到1630年3月，由于狂欢节庆祝导致卫生防疫松懈，疫情开始大爆发。1631年的春夏季节则爆发了第二波疫情。最终，米兰的13万人口中有6万人死亡，经济生产受到严重影响<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=COVID-19 - The great plague of Lombardy - a not so distant resonance chamber|url=https://www.cebm.net/covid-19/covid-19-the-great-plague-of-lombardy-a-not-so-distant-resonance-chamber/|accessdate=2020-12-20|work=The Centre for Evidence-Based Medicine|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110112915/https://www.cebm.net/covid-19/covid-19-the-great-plague-of-lombardy-a-not-so-distant-resonance-chamber/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

